Master thesis is an independent written research paper proposing scientific solution in the field of law. The thesis shall contain: 
- introduction, containing the description of used methods
- scientific discussion, divided into sections and subsections
- conclusion, consisting of short list of main results of the research and conclusions
- list of references
- summary in foreign language (ca 10 % from the paper)
The limit of the required pages is 60-70.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Bring students into advanced engagement with some issues in law and obtaining highly professional skills by writing an independent research paper.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  To formulate in the framework of research the thesis to be defended, to obtain the skills of critical analyse of different opinions, to present personal opinions with scientific argumentations, to offer solutions of described problems, to research and analyse empirical material, to defend proposed solutions and opinions, to debate the topics, to use different research methods, to formulate the conclusions and opinions based on the material studied during the research.
